{
  "texts": [
    "Token-level F1 scores (on a 1-100 scale) between human annotations, large language models (LLMs), and non-neural baseline models.",
    "Baselines random, claim, and query are included for comparison.",
    "ann 1 (LS) refers to annotations created in Label Studio, while ann 2 denotes annotations collected through the custom annotation interface.tively, against the annotations created in Label Studio -surpassing even the human-human agreement.",
    "However, it should be emphasized that these scores are calculated only on samples where LLM annotations were generated correctly and human annotations were available.",
    "All the non-neural baseline methods proves to be weak, as all of them have F1-score less then 18."
  ]
}